{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0149E814YAPr4XtS8WqrwWQ2","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014vtUVi4nY48iWc6BbgrNq1","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n elasticsearch create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"# Elasticsearch Upgrade & Migration Plan\n\n**Cluster:** es-cluster | **Current Version:** 8.11.1 | **License:** Basic\n**Reviewed:** 2026-06-14 | **Status:** DRAFT — awaiting SRE lead approval\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Cluster Topology\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| StatefulSet | es-cluster, 3/3 replicas (Parallel pod management) |\n| Node names | es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2 |\n| Node roles | master + data + ingest (combined, all nodes) |\n| Node attribute | node.attr.tier = hot |\n| Cluster health | GREEN (3 primary shards, 3 replicas, 0 unassigned) |\n| Update strategy | OnDelete (manual rolling restarts required) |\n\n### 1.2 Image & Resources\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| Image | docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1 |\n| CPU request/limit | 500m / 1 |\n| Memory request/limit | 1Gi / 2Gi |\n| JVM heap | -Xms512m -Xmx512m |\n| Data PVC | 5Gi ReadWriteOnce per node |\n\n### 1.3 elasticsearch.yml (ConfigMap: es-config)\n\\`\\`\\`yaml\ncluster.name: es-cluster\nnode.name: \\${POD_NAME}\nnode.roles: [master, data, ingest]\nnode.attr.tier: hot\nnetwork.host: 0.0.0.0\nnode.store.allow_mmap: false\ndiscovery.seed_hosts:\n  - es-cluster-0.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-1.es-cluster\n  - es-cluster-2.es-cluster\ncluster.initial_master_nodes:\n  - es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, es-cluster-2\nxpack.security.enabled: false\nxpack.security.http.ssl.enabled: false\nxpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled: false\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### 1.4 Cluster Settings (Dynamic)\n- Persistent overrides: NONE\n- Transient overrides: NONE\n\n### 1.5 Indices\n| Index | Shards | Replicas | Routing Constraint |\n|-------|--------|----------|--------------------|\n| audit-index | 3 | 1 | require.tier=hot; _tier_preference=data_content |\n\n### 1.6 ILM Policies (User-defined)\n- **180-days-default**: hot (rollover 30d/50gb) → warm at 2d (forcemerge 1 seg, shrink to 1 shard) → cold at 30d → delete at 180d\n- Built-in x-pack policies present (deprecation-indexing, monitoring-8, fleet, ml, slm, watcher, logs, metrics, synthetics) — none currently applied to live indices\n\n### 1.7 Security\n- xpack.security.enabled = **false** (no authentication, no TLS on HTTP or transport)\n- xpack.security.http.ssl.enabled = false\n- xpack.security.transport.ssl.enabled = false\n- License tier: **Basic**\n\n---\n\n## 2. Risks & Gaps Identified\n\n### CRITICAL\n**C1 — Security disabled (xpack.security.enabled: false)**\nAll three nodes expose unauthenticated HTTP on port 9200 with no TLS. Any client inside the cluster can read/write/delete indices without credentials. This must be remediated before or during the upgrade.\n\n**C2 — No snapshot repository configured**\nThere is no registered snapshot repository. A snapshot/restore path is required before any destructive upgrade operation. Without it, recovery from a failed upgrade means rebuilding the cluster from scratch.\n\n### HIGH\n**H1 — cluster.initial_master_nodes still set**\nThis bootstrap setting is only needed for the very first cluster formation. Leaving it in place after the cluster is running is harmless in 8.x but is explicitly deprecated in 9.x and may trigger warnings or startup failures. It must be removed before a major-version upgrade.\n\n**H2 — Combined node roles (no dedicated masters)**\nAll nodes are simultaneously master-eligible, data, and ingest. During a rolling restart an unhealthy node can trigger a master re-election while also losing data shards. For a 3-node cluster this is the minimum viable topology; upgrading to 5+ nodes and separating master-only nodes is strongly recommended before a 9.x upgrade.\n\n**H3 — JVM heap too small for production**\n512 MiB heap (-Xms512m -Xmx512m) is below the 1 GiB minimum recommended for any non-trivial workload. Under upgrade the old and new nodes co-exist briefly and pressure can cause GC pauses or OOM kills.\n\n### MEDIUM\n**M1 — PVC size (5Gi) likely insufficient**\nThe current data volume is 5Gi per node. Elasticsearch recommends leaving 15–25% free. Before upgrading, confirm actual disk usage with _cat/allocation and resize PVCs or add nodes if necessary.\n\n**M2 — OnDelete update strategy requires manual coordination**\nThe StatefulSet update strategy is OnDelete. Pods are NOT automatically restarted after a spec update. Each pod must be manually deleted in reverse ordinal order (2→1→0). The team must have a runbook and confirmed maintenance window before proceeding.\n\n**M3 — audit-index requires.tier=hot constraint**\nThe shard allocation filter \\`routing.allocation.require.tier: hot\\` pins all shards to nodes with node.attr.tier=hot. If any node is retired or reclassified during topology changes, shards will become unassigned and the cluster will turn YELLOW. Review this constraint before scaling out.\n\n**M4 — No warm/cold tier nodes**\nThe ILM policy 180-days-default references a warm and cold phase, but there are no nodes with tier=warm or tier=cold. The policy is defined but will stall at the warm transition for any index it manages until warm-tier nodes are added.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Upgrade Target\n\n**Recommended path:** 8.11.1 → 8.17.x (latest 8.x GA) before considering 9.x\n- Elasticsearch requires upgrading through every minor version when crossing major boundaries; 8.17.x is the mandatory stepping stone before 9.0.\n- Check https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/current/upgrade.html for current compatibility matrix.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Pre-Upgrade Checklist (must complete before touching the cluster)\n\n- [ ] **C2** Register a snapshot repository and take a full snapshot of all indices\n  \\`\\`\\`\n  PUT /_snapshot/backup-repo { ... }\n  PUT /_snapshot/backup-repo/pre-upgrade-snapshot\n  \\`\\`\\`\n- [ ] **C1** Plan TLS/auth enablement: generate CA, node certs, set bootstrap password, update all client connection strings\n- [ ] **H1** Remove cluster.initial_master_nodes from es-config ConfigMap (safe once cluster is formed)\n- [ ] **H3** Increase JVM heap to at least 1g (update ES_JAVA_OPTS=-Xms1g -Xmx1g in StatefulSet env)\n- [ ] **M1** Check disk usage: \\`kubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -s 'http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/allocation?v'\\`; expand PVCs or add nodes if >70% used\n- [ ] Run deprecation API and resolve all issues: \\`GET /_migration/deprecations\\`\n- [ ] Enable shard allocation throttling to safe values:\n  \\`\\`\\`\n  PUT /_cluster/settings\n  { \\\"persistent\\\": { \\\"cluster.routing.allocation.cluster_concurrent_rebalance\\\": \\\"1\\\",\n                    \\\"indices.recovery.max_bytes_per_sec\\\": \\\"100mb\\\" } }\n  \\`\\`\\`\n- [ ] Confirm maintenance window with team; notify downstream consumers of read-only period\n\n---\n\n## 5. Upgrade Procedure (Rolling, OnDelete Strategy)\n\n### Step 1 — Disable shard allocation\n\\`\\`\\`\nPUT /_cluster/settings\n{ \\\"persistent\\\": { \\\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\\\": \\\"primaries\\\" } }\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 2 — Update the StatefulSet image\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch set image statefulset/es-cluster elasticsearch=docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.17.X\n\\`\\`\\`\n(The OnDelete strategy means no pods restart yet.)\n\n### Step 3 — Update es-config ConfigMap\n- Remove cluster.initial_master_nodes\n- Update JVM heap if not done in pre-flight\n- Add security config if enabling TLS in this window\nApply: \\`kubectl -n elasticsearch apply -f es-config.yaml\\`\n\n### Step 4 — Rolling restart (reverse ordinal order)\nRepeat for each node, starting at es-cluster-2:\n\\`\\`\\`bash\n# Delete pod (triggers restart with new image + config)\nkubectl -n elasticsearch delete pod es-cluster-2\n\n# Wait for pod to become Ready\nkubectl -n elasticsearch wait pod/es-cluster-2 --for=condition=Ready --timeout=300s\n\n# Verify cluster health is GREEN before proceeding\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -s 'http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/health?pretty'\n\\`\\`\\`\nRepeat for es-cluster-1, then es-cluster-0.\n\n### Step 5 — Re-enable shard allocation\n\\`\\`\\`\nPUT /_cluster/settings\n{ \\\"persistent\\\": { \\\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\\\": null } }\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n### Step 6 — Verify\n\\`\\`\\`bash\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -s 'http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/nodes?v'\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -s 'http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cluster/health?pretty'\nkubectl -n elasticsearch exec curl-test -- curl -s 'http://es-http.elasticsearch.svc:9200/_cat/shards?v'\n\\`\\`\\`\nExpected: all nodes show new version, cluster GREEN, 0 unassigned shards.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Security Enablement Plan (separate change, recommend before upgrade)\n\nEnabling xpack.security on an existing cluster with security disabled is a breaking change requiring a full cluster restart. Recommended approach:\n\n1. Take a snapshot (always before a full restart)\n2. Update es-config to set xpack.security.enabled: true; generate and distribute TLS certs for transport layer (required when security is enabled)\n3. Perform a full cluster restart (delete all pods; with Parallel podManagementPolicy they restart together)\n4. Set bootstrap.password, then set permanent user passwords via the Elasticsearch security API\n5. Update all clients (application connection strings, health probes) to pass credentials and use HTTPS\n\nAlternatively: stand up a new secured cluster and reindex into it, then cut traffic over. This avoids a full restart on a running cluster.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Rollback Plan\n\nIf the upgrade fails mid-way:\n1. Re-enable shard allocation if disabled: \\`PUT /_cluster/settings {\\\"persistent\\\":{\\\"cluster.routing.allocation.enable\\\":null}}\\`\n2. Revert the StatefulSet image to 8.11.1: \\`kubectl -n elasticsearch set image statefulset/es-cluster elasticsearch=docker.elastic.co/elasticsearch/elasticsearch:8.11.1\\`\n3. Delete each upgraded pod in reverse order; wait for Ready before proceeding\n4. If data corruption is suspected, restore from the pre-upgrade snapshot\n\n---\n\n## 8. Post-Upgrade Follow-ups\n\n- Remove throttling cluster settings applied in pre-flight\n- Update monitoring dashboards/alerts for the new version\n- Verify ILM policy 180-days-default warm/cold transitions (add warm-tier nodes or update policy if warm/cold phases are not needed)\n- Schedule next upgrade review (8.17 → 9.x path) once 9.0 GA stabilizes\n- Evaluate upgrading license to Gold/Platinum if RBAC, field-level security, or alerting features are needed\n\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap with migration plan"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1963,"cache_read_input_tokens":41292,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1963},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"64ab76ce-a36e-41e9-b626-fb56e47f455a","uuid":"769dc30d-77df-420f-b234-2dc8f5ce8255","request_id":"req_011Cc2fPWNbF9e7hHzrVueAw"}
